Sentencas: The polarization resistance of idealized, branched, composite cathodes was modeled using a two-dimensional finite element calculation.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: The model structures consisted of micrometer-scale columns and nanoscale branches of ionically conducting materials that were coated with a mixed-conducting material.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: The structures approximate an ionic-conductor matrix infiltrated first with the same ionic-conductor material and then with a mixed conductor.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Increasing the length of the ionically conducting nanobranches, and hence, the surface area of the infiltrated mixed conductor, resulted in a factor of similar to 10 polarization resistance decrease compared to mixed-conductor-coated columns without ionically conducting nanobranches.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: For many solid oxide fuel cell relevant temperatures (500-900 degrees C), cathode geometries, and materials, the cathode resistance was limited by surface oxygen exchange and hence, was inversely proportional to the mixed-conductor surface area.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: However, for cathode columns or branches with large enough aspect ratios, ionic-conduction losses also limited the polarization resistance.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: The characteristic length of nanostructured cathodes was found to depend on the cathode surface area ratio in addition to the traditional bulk diffusion constant to surface exchange constant ratio (D/k).
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Lastly, the effects of materials properties, particularly ionic conductivity and surface resistance, were investigated and discussed for common cathode materials.
Titulo: Finite-Element Modeling of Idealized Infiltrated Composite Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes
